{"title":"How to make you stupider","link":"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/856596392/0/marginalrevolution~How-to-make-you-stupider.html","date":1704063677000,"content":"<blockquote><p>The Maine official who moved to disqualify former <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.foxnews.com/category/person/donald-trump\" target=\"_blank\">President Donald Trump</a> from the state’s 2024 Republican primary ballot on Thursday visited the White House this year to meet with President Biden and previously referred to the Electoral College as a “relic of white supremacy.”</p></blockquote>\r\n<p>Here is <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.foxnews.com/politics/maine-democrat-barred-trump-ballot-met-biden-year-electoral-college-white-supremacy\" target=\"_blank\">the full story</a>.  This is exactly what I am <em>not</em> going to cover in 2024, so right now you get your miniature, one-time dose.  I am not saying this is not important.  I am saying that reading a lot about it, and commenting on it, will make you stupider.  In fact, the non-elastic Parmenides universe is arranged such that anyone who leaves a comment on this post, no matter what that comments says, will lose two IQ points.</p>\r\n<p>Good luck, and see you next year!</p>\r\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com/marginalrevolution/2023/12/designed-to-make-you-stupid.html\">How to make you stupider</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com\">Marginal REVOLUTION</a>.</p>\r\n<img height=\"1\" width=\"1\" src=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/i/856596392/0/marginalrevolution\" />\r\n<div><a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/28/856596392/marginalrevolution\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/fblike20.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/29/856596392/marginalrev